""
"My biggest 'want' finally goes down the ol' gullet! Pours a slightly hazed yellowy-orange color with a tight, white head. Soft lacing. Aroma is very unique. I got a big whiff of garlic and green onion along with some mossy aromas and a bit of cattiness. Melon and mango as well. I know this is Citra but in the nose, the hop comes off differently and I love it. The flavor legit blew me away. Each sip made me say ""wow"" even louder. The green onion and garlic and cat and hemp is more subdued than the nose. Instead, I get a huge rush of tropical fruit. I've had plenty of Citra brews but this one is very distinguished. It has lots of tropical fruit but the flavor of honeydew melon is so damn rich. Very grassy. I also got a minty flavor that put this one over the top for me. Unlike any other Citra brew I have tried. The body is just hovering around medium. The carbonation is lively. The bitterness isn't too bold but it pricks up quickly. I have had a few from Toppling Goliath and all I have tasted have been phenomenal. This one exceeded my ridiculously lofty expectations. One of the best beers I have had. Enjoyed via bottle."
